At its simplest, a promise is an object that represents the eventual result of an asynchronous operation. This could be anything from loading data from a server, to waiting for user input, to calculating a complex mathematical function. The main advantage of using promises is that they allow us to write more readable and organized code by handling asynchronous operations in a more structured way.

