```javascript
const myPromise = new Promise((resolve, reject) => {
  // Asynchronous operation goes here...
  const myData = fetchDataFromServer();
  if (myData) {
    resolve(myData);
  } else {
    reject("Error: Failed to fetch data!");
  }
});
```

Once we have our promise, we can then use methods like `then()`, `catch()`, and `finally()` to further manipulate the promise and handle various outcomes. Here's an example:

```javascript
